# Task And Issue Format

When creating or updating tasks (especially GitHub Issues), always use the same section order and naming:

1. `Goal`
2. `Tasks`
3. `Done criteria`

## Required Template

Use this exact structure:

```md
## Goal
<one clear objective sentence>

## Tasks
- [ ] <task 1>
- [ ] <task 2>
- [ ] <task 3>

## Done criteria
- [ ] <measurable completion condition 1>
- [ ] <measurable completion condition 2>
```

## Rules

- Use concise, implementation-oriented wording.
- Keep tasks actionable and testable.
- Keep done criteria measurable (no vague "looks good").
- For research tasks, still keep the same three-section format.
- Do not use alternative section names like "Story", "Acceptance criteria", or mixed variants.
